service.name: Double Orphan Pension
service.description: Double Orphan Pension (DOP) is a  non-means tested payment which can be paid to a customer or an Approved Care Organisation (ACO) caring for a young person who is orphaned or unable to be cared for by their parents in certain circumstances.
